    "arxiv_id": "2602.14996",
    "title": "Invariant Gibbs dynamics for the hyperbolic sinh-Gordon model",
    "authors": [
      "Justin Forlano",
      "Younes Zine"
    ],
    "categories": [
      "math.AP",
      "math-ph",
      "math.MP",
      "math.PR"
    ],
    "abstract": "We study the hyperbolic defocusing sinh-Gordon model with parameter $\\beta^2\u003e0$ and its associated Gibbs dynamics on the two-dimensional torus. We establish global well-posedness of the model for a certain range of parameters $\\beta^2\u003e0$ with the corresponding Gibbs measure initial data and prove invariance of the Gibbs measure under the flow, thereby resolving a question posed by Oh, Robert, and Wang (2019). Our physical space approach hinges on developing a novel $L^\\infty$-based well-posedness theory for wave equations with exponential-type nonlinearities, going beyond the classical $L^2$-based framework. This refinement allows us to fully leverage structural properties of Gaussian multiplicative chaos. As a by-product of our method, we also obtain an improved well-posedness theory for the hyperbolic Liouville model.",
    "date": "2026-02",
    "matched_author": "",
